# Quality Gates

Apply these checks before considering any change complete.

## TypeScript (frontend)

- TypeScript strict mode is enabled (`"strict": true` in `frontend/tsconfig.json`). All code must type-check.
- Run `cd frontend && npx tsc --noEmit` to verify — there must be zero errors.
- Do not use `any` unless you can justify it with a comment explaining why the type is unknowable.
- Prefer `z.infer<typeof Schema>` over manually duplicated interfaces.

## Python (backend)

- No bare `except Exception` without at minimum a `print(...)` log — silent swallowing of errors is not acceptable.
- Every write path (INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE) must have `conn.rollback()` in the `except` block and `conn.commit()` on success.
- Do not return `None` from a function that the caller treats as always-truthy without documenting the `None` case.
- No hardcoded connection strings, credentials, or ports — always read from `os.environ`.

## Migrations

- One migration = one concern. Do not bundle unrelated changes.
- File naming: `YYYYMMDD_XX_short-description.sql` (e.g. `20241015_01_add-category-column.sql`).
- All DDL must use safety guards: `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS`, `ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS`, `DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS`, `CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS`.
- Declare ordering with a `-- depends:` comment at the top referencing the previous migration's base name.
- Never modify an already-applied migration file — create a new one.

## Environment & Secrets

- No hardcoded URLs, API keys, hostnames, or ports in source files.
- Frontend env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for browser-exposed vars; server-only vars read in Route Handlers only.
- Backend env: `os.environ.get("VAR", default)` — never `os.environ["VAR"]` without a fallback for optional vars.

## API Consistency

- Any new endpoint must have a corresponding proxy Route Handler in `frontend/app/api/`.
- Response bodies must always use a declared `response_model=` (backend) and a Zod schema (frontend).
- Pagination responses must use `PaginatedResponse[T]` shape: `items`, `total`, `limit`, `offset`.

## Canonical References

- `frontend/tsconfig.json` — strict TypeScript config
- `backend/migrations/20241010_01_receipts_scans.sql` — migration style reference
- `backend/src/repositories/receipts_scans.py` — commit/rollback pattern
- `backend/src/data.py` — Pydantic model naming conventions
